Module mm
Package mm.utilities.ObjectsConf

Class BoxConf

  • java.lang.Object
    • mm.utilities.ObjectsConf.ObjectConf
      • mm.utilities.ObjectsConf.BoxConf
  • public class BoxConf
extends ObjectConf
    Configuration class representing a rectangular box object in the physics simulation. Extends the generic ObjectConf with width, height, density, and friction properties.

    • Field Summary

        Constructs a fully specified BoxConf with position, size, angle, density, and friction.
        Parameters:
        x - X position of the box center (meters).
        y - Y position of the box center (meters).
        width - Width of the box (meters).
        height - Height of the box (meters).
        angle - Rotation angle in degrees.
        density - Density of the box.
        friction - Friction coefficient of the box.

        public BoxConf​(float x,

        Constructs a BoxConf with position, size, and angle. Density and friction are set to -1 by default (static).
        Parameters:
        x - X position of the box center (meters).
        y - Y position of the box center (meters).
        width - Width of the box (meters).
        height - Height of the box (meters).

      • BoxConf

               float y,
               float width,

        Constructs a BoxConf with position and size. Angle is set to 0, density and friction to -1 (static).
        Parameters:
        x - X position of the box center (meters).
        y - Y position of the box center (meters).
        width - Width of the box (meters).
        height - Height of the box (meters).
